WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.594
- …sixty.
- What's wrong?

2
00:00:11.595 --> 00:00:16.432
- Pulse is climbing. 145.160.
- What's happening to her?

3
00:00:16.433 --> 00:00:18.267
- Sweetie. are you okay?
- Mom.

4
00:00:18.268 --> 00:00:20.520
- I'm right here. Mommy's right here.
- Mom. I need you to back up.

5
00:00:20.521 --> 00:00:22.522
- Okay.
- She's in V-fib!

6
00:00:22.523 --> 00:00:25.149
- What's going on?
- Nurse. get her out of here.

7
00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:26.275
Oh. my God.

8
00:00:26.276 --> 00:00:27.568
Mom. you have to help by leaving.

9
00:00:27.569 --> 00:00:28.987
- She's here because of you.
- Come on.

10
00:00:29.613 --> 00:00:31.656
- No. please.
- It's okay. it's okay.

11
00:00:31.657 --> 00:00:34.076
She's gonna be okay. She's gonna be okay.

12
00:00:35.244 --> 00:00:36.452
She's gonna be okay.

13
00:00:36.453 --> 00:00:37.787
- No! She's...
- She's gonna be okay.

14
00:00:37.788 --> 00:00:39.163
- Ready.
- Please.

15
00:00:39.164 --> 00:00:40.499
Charge to 50. Clear!

16
00:00:41.542 --> 00:00:43.000
She's in asystole.

17
00:00:43.001 --> 00:00:44.086
Checking rhythm.

18
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:47.422
- Still in V-fib.
- Charge to 100. Clear!

19
00:00:49.716 --> 00:00:51.968
We have a pulse. BP's coming up.

20
00:00:51.969 --> 00:00:54.638
Oh. God.

21
00:00:58.308 --> 00:00:59.309
Oh. God.

22
00:01:10.612 --> 00:01:11.737
Hello.

23
00:01:11.738 --> 00:01:14.241
Dr. Chen said we've seen the worst of it.

24
00:01:14.908 --> 00:01:17.119
She just needs to rest now.

25
00:01:19.079 --> 00:01:21.206
Best go home. Come back later.

26
00:01:24.877 --> 00:01:26.295
Is your baby in the hospital?

27
00:01:29.047 --> 00:01:30.465
Then don't tell me what's best.

28
00:01:40.017 --> 00:01:43.936
<i>Mary always thought it was
so strange how it happened.</i>

29
00:01:43.937 --> 00:01:46.064
<i>She never did remember missing the pill.</i>

30
00:01:47.566 --> 00:01:50.819
<i>But there it was. The undeniable lines.</i>

31
00:01:52.196 --> 00:01:54.030
<i>At the time. she was far too young.</i>

32
00:01:54.031 --> 00:01:58.035
<i>Her career. and quite a promising one
at that. had only just started.</i>

33
00:01:58.994 --> 00:02:00.454
<i>What would become of her now?</i>

34
00:02:04.541 --> 00:02:07.753
<i>From a young age.
Mary was a naturally gifted storyteller.</i>

35
00:02:08.252 --> 00:02:09.463
<i>Adept at it.</i>

36
00:02:10.422 --> 00:02:12.840
<i>Wielding it to distract
her younger siblings</i>

37
00:02:12.841 --> 00:02:15.886
<i>from the chaos and uncertainty
of their family home.</i>

38
00:02:19.014 --> 00:02:22.767
<i>Stories. especially provocative
and secretive ones</i>

39
00:02:22.768 --> 00:02:23.977
<i>were her escape.</i>

40
00:02:25.270 --> 00:02:26.562
<i>As fate would have it.</i>

41
00:02:26.563 --> 00:02:29.483
<i>Mary's obsession with words
led her to Howard.</i>

42
00:02:31.318 --> 00:02:34.654
<i>Someone who finally understood her.</i>

43
00:02:34.655 --> 00:02:37.782
<i>Every part of her.
Not just the sweet surface</i>

44
00:02:37.783 --> 00:02:42.246
<i>she presented to the world.
but the one she kept safely hidden.</i>

45
00:02:43.872 --> 00:02:46.708
<i>Mary was a naturally gifted storyteller.</i>

46
00:02:47.376 --> 00:02:50.920
<i>And the greatest story she ever told
was that life with Howard.</i>

47
00:02:50.921 --> 00:02:54.800
<i>as a wife and mother.
was her happily ever after.</i>

48
00:03:47.144 --> 00:03:48.228
Mary?

49
00:03:48.770 --> 00:03:50.272
Mary?

50
00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:02.451
What time is it?

51
00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:04.745
Just after 2:00.

52
00:04:06.955 --> 00:04:08.749
She just hasn't woken up yet.

53
00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:12.294
The nurses keep coming in to check on her.

54
00:04:13.754 --> 00:04:18.382
They gave me this long list
of cardiologists to look at.

55
00:04:21.970 --> 00:04:24.931
In case there's any long-term
damage to her heart.

56
00:04:24.932 --> 00:04:26.600
Oh. Mary. I'm so sorry.

57
00:04:27.309 --> 00:04:30.853
Where are the kids?
Are they still here?

58
00:04:30.854 --> 00:04:33.941
No. I took Junie
and Marcus home last night.

59
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:36.485
And Howard?

60
00:04:37.194 --> 00:04:38.903
I haven't seen him all day.

61
00:04:40.781 --> 00:04:43.617
Marcus wanted me
to make sure that you have this.

62
00:04:44.326 --> 00:04:45.536
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

63
00:04:49.164 --> 00:04:51.165
Can we talk about the pills?

64
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:56.421
Mary Simpson?

65
00:04:57.005 --> 00:04:59.298
- Yes?
- You need to come with us.

66
00:04:59.299 --> 00:05:01.092
Okay. What…

67
00:05:01.093 --> 00:05:02.927
What should I do? I can call a lawyer.

68
00:05:02.928 --> 00:05:04.513
Yeah. just stay with her.

69
00:05:05.764 --> 00:05:06.765
I love you.

70
00:05:08.183 --> 00:05:09.393
Thank you.

71
00:05:10.435 --> 00:05:11.895
- Call me.
- Okay.

72
00:05:14.690 --> 00:05:16.440
<i>I said some things
that weren't true.</i>

73
00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:20.027
<i>and it distracted everyone
from what really matters.</i>

74
00:05:20.028 --> 00:05:21.737
<i>Finding who killed my mom.</i>

75
00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:24.032
<i>Our whole family.
we just want this nightmare over.</i>

76
00:05:25.033 --> 00:05:26.784
<i>During this morning's press conference.</i>

77
00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:28.035
- <i>the Hennessey family…</i>
- Ma'am?

78
00:05:28.036 --> 00:05:30.997
<i>…announced a $50.000 reward
for any information</i>

79
00:05:30.998 --> 00:05:33.791
<i>that could lead to an arrest
in the murder of Nancy Hennessey.</i>

80
00:05:33.792 --> 00:05:36.628
<i>The family insists the victim's
husband is innocent.</i>

81
00:05:41.508 --> 00:05:44.385
Mrs. Simpson? My name is Kavita Sahni.

82
00:05:44.386 --> 00:05:47.680
I work for the Department of Children
and Family Services.

83
00:05:47.681 --> 00:05:51.142
We've launched a formal investigation
into what happened to your daughter.

84
00:05:51.143 --> 00:05:53.437
This is the emergency protective order.

85
00:05:55.063 --> 00:05:58.357
While our investigation is ongoing
and for the safety of your children.

86
00:05:58.358 --> 00:06:00.026
you'll be required to leave the home.

87
00:06:00.027 --> 00:06:03.363
And you're not to have any unsupervised
contact with your minor children.

88
00:06:05.657 --> 00:06:06.658
What?

89
00:06:07.451 --> 00:06:09.577
- Any violation of this court order…
- You can't do that.

90
00:06:09.578 --> 00:06:11.788
- You can't do that.
- …will lead to your arrest.

91
00:06:12.956 --> 00:06:14.332
No. I'm…

92
00:06:14.333 --> 00:06:15.958
I'm a good mother.

93
00:06:15.959 --> 00:06:18.211
You're free to request
a detention hearing with the judge.

94
00:06:18.212 --> 00:06:21.547
Tell her… Howard. you have to tell her
I am a good mother.

95
00:06:21.548 --> 00:06:23.382
This was one awful mistake.

96
00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:25.219
- You mind if I speak with my wife alone?
- Yeah.

97
00:06:26.970 --> 00:06:29.096
We can fight this. Howard.

98
00:06:29.097 --> 00:06:30.848
You have to tell her that…

99
00:06:30.849 --> 00:06:33.059
- Eleanor can help us with a lawyer.
- Where is it?

100
00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:34.645
Where's what?

101
00:06:35.646 --> 00:06:37.271
Artemis woke me up
because she wet the bed.

102
00:06:37.272 --> 00:06:38.607
She was looking for you.

103
00:06:39.775 --> 00:06:41.109
Searched the whole house.

104
00:06:42.361 --> 00:06:44.946
I assumed you'd passed out on the couch.

105
00:06:44.947 --> 00:06:47.907
doomscrolling or whatever
the hell it is you do at night.

106
00:06:47.908 --> 00:06:50.327
And then I checked the office.

107
00:06:51.036 --> 00:06:53.038
The mess you made…

108
00:06:54.998 --> 00:06:57.251
You took something from my closet.

109
00:07:09.137 --> 00:07:11.390
Those pills are on the highest shelf.

110
00:07:14.518 --> 00:07:16.728
There's no way that the girls
could ever reach them.

111
00:07:17.563 --> 00:07:19.648
- And you know that.
- Mary.

112
00:07:20.232 --> 00:07:21.233
You did it.

113
00:07:24.069 --> 00:07:27.280
You poisoned our baby.

114
00:07:27.281 --> 00:07:28.948
Why would I do something like that?

115
00:07:28.949 --> 00:07:32.285
Because I know. Howard.

116
00:07:32.286 --> 00:07:36.372
I know that you killed Nancy.

117
00:07:36.373 --> 00:07:37.875
And now I know it

118
00:07:38.667 --> 00:07:43.713
with every single part of me.

119
00:07:43.714 --> 00:07:48.509
They're about to lock you up
for a few pep pills in a tin of mints.

120
00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:51.763
And they don't even know the half of it.

121
00:07:52.306 --> 00:07:54.266
You may never see the girls again.

122
00:07:55.517 --> 00:07:58.020
You motherfucker!

123
00:07:59.479 --> 00:08:01.480
You fucking liar!

124
00:08:01.481 --> 00:08:03.232
- Mary! Please stop!
- You fucking monster!

125
00:08:03.233 --> 00:08:04.400
- You need to calm down.
- Liar!

126
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:06.235
- How dare you take them?
- Ma'am. Ma'am!

127
00:08:06.236 --> 00:08:08.446
- How dare… He poisoned my child!
- Hey! What…

128
00:08:08.447 --> 00:08:09.614
You have to listen to me!

129
00:08:09.615 --> 00:08:12.158
- My wife is just upset.
- He poisoned my baby!

130
00:08:12.159 --> 00:08:13.868
Officers. my wife is just upset.

131
00:08:13.869 --> 00:08:15.620
- You fucking liar!
- Please. escort Mrs. Simpson...

132
00:08:15.621 --> 00:08:17.997
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!
I will take her. She can come with me.

133
00:08:17.998 --> 00:08:20.208
I will not leave my girls with him. Ellie!

134
00:08:20.209 --> 00:08:22.293
- No!
- Then let me just... Stop. Mary. Stop.

135
00:08:22.294 --> 00:08:24.170
- Look at me! Look at me! Stop. Stop!
- My girls...

136
00:08:24.171 --> 00:08:27.298
- You have to stop. We'll figure it out.
- But he poisoned…

137
00:08:27.299 --> 00:08:28.591
Stop.

138
00:08:28.592 --> 00:08:31.386
- You're making it worse. Please.
- My girls. my girls…

139
00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:34.264
Let go of her. Please. please.

140
00:08:35.349 --> 00:08:37.016
- He poisoned…
- It's okay. it's okay.

141
00:08:37.017 --> 00:08:39.061
It's okay.

142
00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:41.688
Mary…

143
00:08:50.697 --> 00:08:54.200
This book was out of print
before it even hit the bookstore.

144
00:08:54.201 --> 00:08:57.537
Howard is the only person in the world
with this translation of 'Catullus V'.

145
00:08:57.538 --> 00:09:00.331
And he gave it to me years ago
when we first started dating.

146
00:09:00.332 --> 00:09:03.543
He gave Nancy the same one.

147
00:09:03.544 --> 00:09:07.380
And you knew none of this when
I stopped by your house yesterday?

148
00:09:07.381 --> 00:09:10.217
I found out about
all of this after you left.

149
00:09:11.468 --> 00:09:13.095
He's a sociopath.

150
00:09:14.012 --> 00:09:15.096
He's a liar.

151
00:09:15.097 --> 00:09:17.014
You learn that yesterday too?

152
00:09:18.517 --> 00:09:22.563
You'd be surprised what you can
fool yourself into thinking sometimes.

153
00:09:23.522 --> 00:09:25.816
Only see what you wanna see
and not what's there.

154
00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:28.067
But this? This ring?

155
00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:31.028
This has to be probable cause. Detective.
You can use this.

156
00:09:31.029 --> 00:09:33.030
You can bring him in.
You can get his prints.

157
00:09:33.031 --> 00:09:35.867
Compare it to anything you have
from the crime scene.

158
00:09:35.868 --> 00:09:37.077
I'm telling you the truth.

159
00:09:37.578 --> 00:09:40.789
My husband was sleeping
with my best friend.

160
00:09:41.999 --> 00:09:43.709
He killed her.

161
00:09:44.918 --> 00:09:47.753
How else would Nancy's ring
be in my house?

162
00:09:50.132 --> 00:09:51.383
Excuse me.

163
00:09:53.218 --> 00:09:55.219
Thank you. Jodi. for bringing her in.

164
00:09:55.220 --> 00:09:58.598
- Please. join us.
- No. I-I don't have anything to add.

165
00:09:58.599 --> 00:10:00.976
Okay.
But this is only gonna take a minute.

166
00:10:14.031 --> 00:10:15.032
Hmm.

167
00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:20.579
Ms. Bouchet.
do you recognize any of these items?

168
00:10:23.332 --> 00:10:28.462
Yes. these are Nancy's things.
Yeah. Nancy Lauren Hennessey.

169
00:10:33.133 --> 00:10:35.302
I don't understand. Is this evidence?

170
00:10:42.309 --> 00:10:43.726
What's going on?

171
00:10:43.727 --> 00:10:45.645
Howard got to you?

172
00:10:45.646 --> 00:10:49.899
If you're asking how what's in this box
came to be in my possession. then…

173
00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:52.528
Yes. your husband
came in this morning. but…

174
00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:55.071
Help me clarify something.

175
00:10:55.072 --> 00:10:58.534
How exactly did these items
get into your house?

176
00:10:59.368 --> 00:11:01.954
Did he steal them from
Mrs. Hennessey or did you?

177
00:11:06.917 --> 00:11:08.544
It's not what it looks like.

178
00:11:09.127 --> 00:11:13.047
- Oh. Mary. What did you do?
- She...

179
00:11:13.048 --> 00:11:16.342
She would never have even noticed
that any of it was gone.

180
00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:18.970
- Nancy had so much.
- Oh. my God.

181
00:11:18.971 --> 00:11:22.431
Your husband says you were jealous
and obsessed with Mrs. Hennessey.

182
00:11:22.432 --> 00:11:23.516
Were you?

183
00:11:23.517 --> 00:11:25.102
This is what he wants.

184
00:11:26.520 --> 00:11:29.647
- He's trying to distract you.
- He says this is why you're accusing him

185
00:11:29.648 --> 00:11:32.650
- of having an affair with her.
- No. he seduced her.

186
00:11:32.651 --> 00:11:36.113
He killed her.
He is the bad guy. I am not.

187
00:11:40.409 --> 00:11:43.996
You know. I've been doing…
…this job a long time.

188
00:11:44.997 --> 00:11:49.041
I've met a lot of loved ones
in a lot of different relationships.

189
00:11:49.042 --> 00:11:53.296
And this thing. what the three of you had.

190
00:11:53.297 --> 00:11:57.968
I'm not even sure what to call it.
but it wasn't a friendship.

191
00:12:04.349 --> 00:12:05.559
Thank you for stopping by.

192
00:12:28.040 --> 00:12:30.625
- <i>Mom?</i>
- Hey. hi.

193
00:12:30.626 --> 00:12:33.211
Mom. What's… What's going on?
Dad said you're not coming home.

194
00:12:33.212 --> 00:12:34.795
- Where are you?
- <i>I'm at the hospital.</i>

195
00:12:34.796 --> 00:12:36.381
Junie wanted to see Artemis.

196
00:12:37.007 --> 00:12:39.592
- Is she okay?
<i>- Y-Yeah.</i>

197
00:12:39.593 --> 00:12:40.801
Yeah. she's awake.

198
00:12:40.802 --> 00:12:43.555
<i>Doctor said she's gonna be fine.
She can go home tomorrow night.</i>

199
00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:48.100
- <i>Thank God.</i>
- What's going on?

200
00:12:48.101 --> 00:12:51.480
I will explain everything
as soon as I can. Okay. honey?

201
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:53.565
<i>Can you do something for me?</i>

202
00:12:55.192 --> 00:12:56.610
Okay. yeah. What?

203
00:12:57.236 --> 00:12:59.613
Do not leave your sisters
alone with your father.

204
00:13:00.239 --> 00:13:02.115
You cannot let them out of your sight.

205
00:13:02.741 --> 00:13:03.909
<i>Can you do that?</i>

206
00:13:06.495 --> 00:13:08.829
Uh. Mom. I… I gotta go.

207
00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:10.748
I know that is a lot to ask.

208
00:13:10.749 --> 00:13:12.208
I know.

209
00:13:12.209 --> 00:13:15.170
Mom. whatever's going on…
I'm on your side.

210
00:13:35.357 --> 00:13:36.775
I talked to Marcus.

211
00:13:37.401 --> 00:13:40.362
Artie's awake. and she's doing better.

212
00:13:42.489 --> 00:13:43.574
That's good.

213
00:13:50.581 --> 00:13:54.126
I set a meeting in the morning
with a PI who works with my attorneys.

214
00:13:55.711 --> 00:13:59.172
He has the photos from the crime scene.

215
00:13:59.173 --> 00:14:03.677
and he's gonna see if we can find some
connection between Howard and the murder.

216
00:14:04.219 --> 00:14:08.890
Because at this point.
only hard evidence will convince them.

217
00:14:08.891 --> 00:14:14.021
Right. Because of me.
our words don't really matter anymore.

218
00:14:20.944 --> 00:14:21.987
You're mad at me.

219
00:14:22.571 --> 00:14:23.780
I'm not.

220
00:14:24.656 --> 00:14:27.159
- I don't hate Nancy.
- I know you don't.

221
00:14:33.874 --> 00:14:36.834
Don't you wanna know why
I took those things because...

222
00:14:36.835 --> 00:14:40.838
Do you even know why? Really?

223
00:14:46.261 --> 00:14:47.429
It's my mother.

224
00:14:48.222 --> 00:14:51.849
I'm sure she's just calling to see
if I've run off with Robert

225
00:14:51.850 --> 00:14:54.269
and forever tarnished
the Bouchet family name.

226
00:14:56.063 --> 00:14:57.105
How is Robert?

227
00:14:57.648 --> 00:14:58.982
I wouldn't know.

228
00:15:03.153 --> 00:15:05.030
We have an early start tomorrow morning.

229
00:15:18.919 --> 00:15:21.838
Do you want anything?
I could get the menu.

230
00:15:21.839 --> 00:15:23.714
They make a quality strawberry milkshake.

231
00:15:23.715 --> 00:15:26.175
No. thanks.
That's not necessary.

232
00:15:26.176 --> 00:15:27.760
Do you have the photos?

233
00:15:27.761 --> 00:15:29.429
Down to business. I like that.

234
00:15:30.889 --> 00:15:33.808
You're not squeamish. are you?
These are pretty graphic.

235
00:15:33.809 --> 00:15:35.561
I need to see what he did to her.

236
00:15:56.707 --> 00:15:59.877
Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

237
00:16:00.961 --> 00:16:02.378
- Thank you.
- Sure.

238
00:16:02.379 --> 00:16:05.591
Could you show us in person?
The crime scene?

239
00:16:06.884 --> 00:16:10.094
That wasn't what we agreed on.
I could lose my license.

240
00:16:10.095 --> 00:16:12.638
Mary. Everything we need
is in these photos.

241
00:16:12.639 --> 00:16:13.765
No. it's not.

242
00:16:14.850 --> 00:16:17.268
What exactly is your goal here?

243
00:16:17.269 --> 00:16:19.312
The man who did this
is not a professional.

244
00:16:19.313 --> 00:16:21.523
I'm… I know him.

245
00:16:22.691 --> 00:16:24.776
And if he made a mistake. I will find it.

246
00:16:38.624 --> 00:16:40.833
This is it. The dead zone.

247
00:16:40.834 --> 00:16:43.044
The victim was murdered here.

248
00:16:43.045 --> 00:16:45.880
Her name was Nancy. not "the victim."

249
00:16:45.881 --> 00:16:48.591
You really want me
to say her name while I do this?

250
00:16:49.843 --> 00:16:51.470
Your killer gets the victim here.

251
00:16:51.970 --> 00:16:55.432
Trajectory of the blood splatter
tells us he's at least six feet tall.

252
00:16:56.099 --> 00:16:57.683
He gets her into this spot.

253
00:16:57.684 --> 00:17:00.937
She can't run. and he shoves her.

254
00:17:00.938 --> 00:17:04.899
Based on the skull fracture. we know once
was all it took to get the job done.

255
00:17:04.900 --> 00:17:06.817
And then she falls here.

256
00:17:06.818 --> 00:17:09.654
Wait. I thought the police said
they found her body by the water.

257
00:17:09.655 --> 00:17:10.780
They did.

258
00:17:10.781 --> 00:17:14.200
Yeah. He dragged her about 30 feet east.

259
00:17:14.201 --> 00:17:15.785
That's where he dumped her body.

260
00:17:15.786 --> 00:17:20.499
It's easier
to pull dead weight by the ankles.

261
00:17:24.670 --> 00:17:26.629
But here's the interesting part.

262
00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:30.758
<i>About half way.
he stopped pulling by both her ankles.</i>

263
00:17:30.759 --> 00:17:32.260
How do you know?

264
00:17:32.261 --> 00:17:36.430
Well. the patterns of
the blood smear changes right here.

265
00:17:36.431 --> 00:17:37.682
I have a hunch.

266
00:17:37.683 --> 00:17:40.685
Dragging the victim that whole distance

267
00:17:40.686 --> 00:17:43.605
with both his hands
was probably too much for the guy.

268
00:17:44.314 --> 00:17:48.986
It looks like he used his right hand
to drag her the rest of the way.

269
00:17:50.153 --> 00:17:51.821
Not because he's weak.

270
00:17:51.822 --> 00:17:54.949
But I think your killer
has some type of injury.

271
00:17:54.950 --> 00:17:56.869
Maybe a bad back or a bum left shoulder.

272
00:18:15.971 --> 00:18:17.513
You're sure no one's home?

273
00:18:17.514 --> 00:18:19.390
Artie hasn't been discharged yet.

274
00:18:19.391 --> 00:18:21.559
and Marcus said that they're all
still with her at the hospital.

275
00:18:21.560 --> 00:18:23.227
You're not supposed to be here. Mary.

276
00:18:23.228 --> 00:18:25.229
Maybe we just find
the doctor's office tomorrow?

277
00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:28.733
No. I can do this. I can do it.

278
00:18:28.734 --> 00:18:31.319
You don't have to prove anything to me.

279
00:18:31.320 --> 00:18:32.654
I know I don't.

280
00:18:36.074 --> 00:18:37.366
In and out.

281
00:18:37.367 --> 00:18:38.744
- Okay.
- I'll be right here.

282
00:19:34.174 --> 00:19:35.926
Well. this wasn't very smart.

283
00:19:36.677 --> 00:19:39.679
Imagine what would happen if
Child Services made an unannounced visit.

284
00:19:39.680 --> 00:19:41.305
You'd be in a heap of trouble.

285
00:19:41.306 --> 00:19:43.725
This is still my house.

286
00:19:49.064 --> 00:19:51.024
What do you have there?

287
00:19:54.152 --> 00:19:56.738
I hate this. Mary.

288
00:19:57.531 --> 00:19:58.907
You're afraid of me.

289
00:19:59.700 --> 00:20:02.118
Look at you. You're shaking like a leaf.

290
00:20:02.119 --> 00:20:03.453
You killed Nancy.

291
00:20:04.204 --> 00:20:06.038
I wish you'd stop saying that.

292
00:20:06.039 --> 00:20:08.875
They know. The police.

293
00:20:08.876 --> 00:20:13.297
They know that the killer
had an injured left shoulder.

294
00:20:14.047 --> 00:20:15.465
They know.

295
00:20:16.550 --> 00:20:18.552
Ah. my medical records.

296
00:20:19.803 --> 00:20:21.013
Is that your plan?

297
00:20:21.972 --> 00:20:25.808
To take those to the police
and dazzle them with the news

298
00:20:25.809 --> 00:20:27.936
that I have the world's
most common gym injury?

299
00:20:30.689 --> 00:20:34.066
Can you at least sit down?
Standing feels so combative.

300
00:20:34.067 --> 00:20:36.486
I-I just wanna talk
for a minute like we always have.

301
00:20:38.447 --> 00:20:40.782
I-I think you owe that to me at least.

302
00:20:41.825 --> 00:20:43.452
You know me better than anybody.

303
00:20:44.453 --> 00:20:45.454
I don't.

304
00:20:46.455 --> 00:20:47.664
I don't know you.

305
00:20:50.042 --> 00:20:53.462
The man that I married.
the man that I…

306
00:20:54.379 --> 00:20:56.256
The man that I fell in love with.

307
00:20:57.925 --> 00:21:01.969
He never would've done
the awful things that you have done.

308
00:21:01.970 --> 00:21:03.888
I haven't done anything awful.

309
00:21:03.889 --> 00:21:05.307
That's you.

310
00:21:06.683 --> 00:21:09.644
Don't you see?
You're tearing this family apart.

311
00:21:09.645 --> 00:21:11.354
No. stop that.

312
00:21:11.355 --> 00:21:12.522
Stop it.

313
00:21:12.523 --> 00:21:15.107
- Stop what?
- Stop twisting things around on me.

314
00:21:15.108 --> 00:21:17.109
What is your endgame here?
What do you want?

315
00:21:17.110 --> 00:21:21.114
I want you out of my house
and I want you away from my children.

316
00:21:22.324 --> 00:21:24.909
And I want you to rot for what you did.

317
00:21:24.910 --> 00:21:25.911
And then what?

318
00:21:26.495 --> 00:21:29.248
With me out of the picture.
it's not as if you'd be granted custody.

319
00:21:29.831 --> 00:21:32.709
Nor anyone
in your colorfully unstable family.

320
00:21:33.210 --> 00:21:37.630
I can't see a judge
sending the girls to Grandma's pot farm

321
00:21:37.631 --> 00:21:39.298
after what they've been through.

322
00:21:39.299 --> 00:21:43.261
And with Godmother Eleanor
still a suspect in her friend's death...

323
00:21:43.262 --> 00:21:44.554
You fucking asshole.

324
00:21:44.555 --> 00:21:47.558
I guess that leaves foster care.
And I know that's not what you want.

325
00:21:50.060 --> 00:21:52.104
I still love you. Mary.

326
00:21:52.813 --> 00:21:54.981
despite all your fabulations.

327
00:21:54.982 --> 00:21:57.817
I can still envision us getting past this.

328
00:21:57.818 --> 00:21:59.694
Starting over. starting fresh.

329
00:21:59.695 --> 00:22:01.279
That's what I want.

330
00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:04.575
Leaving here
and going to Ohio as a family.

331
00:22:05.450 --> 00:22:07.076
I know how much you love the children.

332
00:22:08.871 --> 00:22:10.162
More than anything.

333
00:22:10.163 --> 00:22:12.374
We can still be a family. you and I.

334
00:22:13.584 --> 00:22:16.170
Like <i>Chloe and Daphnis</i>.

335
00:22:17.671 --> 00:22:20.424
Troubled. but fated.

336
00:22:24.052 --> 00:22:25.554
God. I used to believe that.

337
00:22:28.432 --> 00:22:30.142
Then I spoke to Jenny.

338
00:22:33.187 --> 00:22:34.688
She showed it to me.

339
00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:37.858
She showed me the scar.

340
00:22:39.318 --> 00:22:40.319
Hmm?

341
00:22:41.486 --> 00:22:44.656
The one that she got
the night she tried to…

342
00:22:45.365 --> 00:22:46.658
to leave you.

343
00:22:48.410 --> 00:22:49.660
Mmm.

344
00:22:49.661 --> 00:22:52.331
The words. Your stories.

345
00:22:54.750 --> 00:22:59.379
That's one thing.
but a scar on a body is proof.

346
00:23:00.589 --> 00:23:03.008
Because that's what you do. right? Right?

347
00:23:04.384 --> 00:23:06.136
You take a fragile woman.

348
00:23:07.095 --> 00:23:12.476
then you hollow her out
until you are all that is left.

349
00:23:14.895 --> 00:23:16.980
There's one thing I don't understand.

350
00:23:18.106 --> 00:23:21.527
Why Nancy. Howard?

351
00:23:24.404 --> 00:23:26.156
You could've had anyone.

352
00:23:27.866 --> 00:23:28.909
Why her?

353
00:23:31.286 --> 00:23:32.996
I'm sorry. Mare.

354
00:23:38.210 --> 00:23:39.336
I'm so sorry.

355
00:23:44.258 --> 00:23:46.926
But I wasn't the one
with a thing for Nancy.

356
00:23:46.927 --> 00:23:48.220
That was you.

357
00:23:52.558 --> 00:23:55.018
- No.
- I know you loved her.

358
00:23:57.062 --> 00:23:59.063
You thought she was so beautiful.

359
00:23:59.064 --> 00:24:01.358
That's why I went along
with your little game.

360
00:24:05.070 --> 00:24:06.989
It was… It was actually quite hot.

361
00:24:07.573 --> 00:24:12.995
watching how turned on
you'd get fantasizing about being her.

362
00:24:15.581 --> 00:24:17.290
<i>Wearing her clothes…</i>

363
00:24:17.291 --> 00:24:19.000
Welcome back. Mr. and Mrs. Hennessey.

364
00:24:19.001 --> 00:24:20.793
Putting on her earrings…

365
00:24:24.089 --> 00:24:26.675
You even wanted
to smell like her.

366
00:24:27.843 --> 00:24:29.595
Please stop.

367
00:24:39.646 --> 00:24:41.190
Remember how much fun we had?

368
00:24:44.610 --> 00:24:45.652
Fuck me.

369
00:24:51.700 --> 00:24:53.493
Tell me how much you want it. Nancy.

370
00:25:04.588 --> 00:25:08.175
Now you take those to Detective Ganz.

371
00:25:09.092 --> 00:25:11.345
you tell her the whole story.

372
00:25:13.514 --> 00:25:15.015
Because if I'm guilty…

373
00:25:17.309 --> 00:25:18.519
so are you.

374
00:25:36.620 --> 00:25:38.914
What happened? What took you so long?

375
00:25:40.499 --> 00:25:41.500
Let's go.

376
00:26:11.780 --> 00:26:13.031
<i>Stop the car.</i>

377
00:26:14.575 --> 00:26:17.702
Ellie. stop the car please.
Ellie. pull over! Stop the car!

378
00:26:17.703 --> 00:26:19.662
- Here?
- Stop the car!

379
00:26:19.663 --> 00:26:20.746
Okay.

380
00:26:20.747 --> 00:26:21.748
Stop.

381
00:26:22.499 --> 00:26:23.500
You okay?

382
00:26:24.585 --> 00:26:25.794
What's happening?

383
00:26:28.589 --> 00:26:29.839
Shit.

384
00:26:29.840 --> 00:26:31.133
Mary!

385
00:26:33.510 --> 00:26:34.845
What are you doing?

386
00:26:35.762 --> 00:26:36.889
Mary. what are you…

387
00:26:37.389 --> 00:26:39.016
What happened?

388
00:26:40.017 --> 00:26:42.476
Please talk to me. Tell me what happened.

389
00:26:42.477 --> 00:26:43.812
I can't do it.

390
00:26:44.980 --> 00:26:46.522
- I can't do it.
- What?

391
00:26:46.523 --> 00:26:48.733
I can't do it. any of it.
I can't go to the police.

392
00:26:48.734 --> 00:26:50.068
What are you talking about?

393
00:26:50.569 --> 00:26:51.570
He wins.

394
00:26:52.070 --> 00:26:53.655
- No. he can't win.
- Howard wins.

395
00:26:55.282 --> 00:26:57.074
I could lose my children.
do you understand?

396
00:26:57.075 --> 00:26:58.951
- I could...
- But if he goes to jail…

397
00:26:58.952 --> 00:27:00.786
He won't. don't you see that?

398
00:27:00.787 --> 00:27:02.998
He's so much smarter than I am. Ellie.

399
00:27:03.498 --> 00:27:05.750
Every move I make. he's two ahead.

400
00:27:05.751 --> 00:27:07.461
He is so much smarter than me.

401
00:27:08.086 --> 00:27:10.380
Why am I even doing any of this?

402
00:27:11.465 --> 00:27:13.174
Nancy thought I was pathetic.

403
00:27:13.175 --> 00:27:14.800
No. Nancy loved you.

404
00:27:14.801 --> 00:27:17.428
Yes. she was fucking my husband!

405
00:27:17.429 --> 00:27:20.849
Howard may be a piece of shit.
but Nancy is not without blame.

406
00:27:21.600 --> 00:27:22.726
She's not.

407
00:27:23.310 --> 00:27:26.145
Ellie. please. I can't.
I cannot lose any more than I have.

408
00:27:26.146 --> 00:27:28.232
I can't lose them. I can't…
I can't.

409
00:27:29.441 --> 00:27:31.777
He… He's a murderer!

410
00:27:32.277 --> 00:27:37.699
He's a fucking murderer.
He murdered our best friend!

411
00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:41.202
That's it. That's all that matters.

412
00:27:41.203 --> 00:27:42.703
I understand that you are tired.

413
00:27:42.704 --> 00:27:45.456
I understand that you are afraid.
I am too.

414
00:27:45.457 --> 00:27:48.042
We're gonna go home.
we're gonna get in bed. we're gonna sleep.

415
00:27:48.043 --> 00:27:50.127
and tomorrow we will wake up. together.

416
00:27:50.128 --> 00:27:53.590
We will go to the police with
Howard's medical records. like we planned.

417
00:27:56.051 --> 00:27:57.219
Please.

418
00:29:28.352 --> 00:29:29.353
Mare.

419
00:29:39.404 --> 00:29:40.405
Mary?

420
00:29:45.619 --> 00:29:46.620
Oh. God.

421
00:29:47.746 --> 00:29:50.581
Mary?

422
00:29:50.582 --> 00:29:52.542
<i>- Hey. you've reached Mary.
- And Junie.</i>

423
00:29:52.543 --> 00:29:53.626
- Shit.
<i>- And me!</i>

424
00:29:53.627 --> 00:29:55.837
- <i>We can't come to the phone right…</i>
- Oh. no.

425
00:29:55.838 --> 00:29:57.797
Please. Mary?

426
00:29:57.798 --> 00:29:59.924
<i>- Hey. you've reached Mary.
- And Junie.</i>

427
00:29:59.925 --> 00:30:01.467
- <i>And me!</i>
- No. please.

428
00:30:01.468 --> 00:30:03.594
<i>Hey. you've reached Mary.</i>

429
00:30:03.595 --> 00:30:05.096
<i>- And Junie.
- And me!</i>

430
00:30:05.097 --> 00:30:07.348
<i>We can't come to the phone right
now. but if you leave a message.</i>

431
00:30:07.349 --> 00:30:10.269
- <i>we'll call you back.</i>
- Mary. where are you?

432
00:30:35.335 --> 00:30:37.129
I won't say a word.

433
00:30:40.716 --> 00:30:42.342
I'm gonna be good.

434
00:30:46.805 --> 00:30:48.265
I promise.

435
00:32:00.963 --> 00:32:01.964
Mary!

436
00:32:03.799 --> 00:32:05.383
- Eleanor. for Christ's sake.
- Where is she?

437
00:32:05.384 --> 00:32:07.552
- You are aware I have neighbors?
- Where is Mary?

438
00:32:07.553 --> 00:32:08.719
She doesn't wanna see you.

439
00:32:08.720 --> 00:32:10.973
What? What did you do?

440
00:32:11.473 --> 00:32:14.600
Nothing. This was her choice.
She came back of her own free will.

441
00:32:14.601 --> 00:32:16.102
She wouldn't.

442
00:32:16.103 --> 00:32:19.814
This might be a foreign concept to you.
but marriages have their ups and downs.

443
00:32:19.815 --> 00:32:22.817
Mary is my wife. I am her husband.
we are a family.

444
00:32:22.818 --> 00:32:23.901
Mary!

445
00:32:23.902 --> 00:32:25.945
And despite what you may think. Eleanor.

446
00:32:25.946 --> 00:32:27.489
you're not a part of this family.

447
00:32:28.156 --> 00:32:30.157
Now get the fuck off my property
before I call the police

448
00:32:30.158 --> 00:32:31.868
and have you arrested for trespassing.

449
00:32:31.869 --> 00:32:33.245
Sh…

450
00:32:34.830 --> 00:32:35.831
Mary!

451
00:32:37.291 --> 00:32:39.293
Oh. my God. Mary?

452
00:32:40.085 --> 00:32:42.336
- What happened?
- Get off my property.

453
00:32:42.337 --> 00:32:45.716
What are you doing? You know what he did.

454
00:32:46.425 --> 00:32:48.594
He killed Nancy.

455
00:32:49.553 --> 00:32:51.220
Don't be a coward. Mary.

456
00:32:51.221 --> 00:32:53.055
- Leave.
- He knows what he did!

457
00:32:53.056 --> 00:32:54.308
- Right now. Leave.
- Mary!

458
00:33:02.232 --> 00:33:03.734
I'm going. I'm going.

459
00:33:30.802 --> 00:33:33.054
<i>Hey. you've reached Mary.</i>

460
00:33:33.055 --> 00:33:34.597
<i>- And Junie.
- And me!</i>

461
00:33:34.598 --> 00:33:37.559
<i>We can't come to the phone right
now. but if you leave a message. we'll…</i>

462
00:33:46.401 --> 00:33:48.611
Ms. Bouchet.
Is Mr. Hennessey expecting you?

463
00:33:48.612 --> 00:33:49.779
Is he home?

464
00:33:49.780 --> 00:33:52.074
- He is but he's not alone.
- It's very urgent.

465
00:33:53.242 --> 00:33:55.327
When have I ever not done what you asked?

466
00:33:56.703 --> 00:33:59.205
- I'm sorry. sir.
- Eleanor. wh-what are you doing here?

467
00:33:59.206 --> 00:34:00.581
I need to talk to you.

468
00:34:00.582 --> 00:34:02.166
- I'm afraid that's not possible.
- It's rea...

469
00:34:02.167 --> 00:34:04.752
As you can see.
my son is circling rock bottom.

470
00:34:04.753 --> 00:34:07.506
- This is important.
- Then have your attorneys reach out.

471
00:34:08.130 --> 00:34:09.757
Howard killed Nancy.

472
00:34:11.092 --> 00:34:12.386
What?

473
00:34:16.849 --> 00:34:20.600
Robert. I'm so sorry.
but he was having an affair with Nancy.

474
00:34:20.601 --> 00:34:23.479
I don't know when it started.
maybe when they were working together.

475
00:34:23.480 --> 00:34:26.566
But he did this. He killed Nancy.

476
00:34:26.567 --> 00:34:28.317
Mary has evidence.

477
00:34:28.318 --> 00:34:30.903
Do you remember the-the Claddagh ring
that Nancy wore?

478
00:34:30.904 --> 00:34:32.196
- Yeah.
- She was wearing it that night.

479
00:34:32.197 --> 00:34:38.078
And Howard took it off of Nancy's dead
body and he hid it. And Mary found it.

480
00:34:38.745 --> 00:34:39.996
Well. it's solved then.

481
00:34:41.248 --> 00:34:44.082
This-This-This can't be true.
It doesn't make any sense.

482
00:34:44.083 --> 00:34:45.334
Robert.

483
00:34:45.335 --> 00:34:47.254
I believe Mary.

484
00:34:54.261 --> 00:34:56.846
Why. uh… Why not take this to the police?

485
00:34:56.847 --> 00:34:59.098
We did. We tried. but it's…

486
00:34:59.099 --> 00:35:03.352
It's very complicated. But one call
from you to the chief of police...

487
00:35:03.353 --> 00:35:04.604
Absolutely not.

488
00:35:04.605 --> 00:35:06.147
Have Constance do it.

489
00:35:06.148 --> 00:35:08.316
I'm sure your mother has sway
with the department.

490
00:35:08.317 --> 00:35:11.195
In Boston. maybe. But this…

491
00:35:11.904 --> 00:35:16.449
You don't understand.
Howard is dangerous. Mary is in danger.

492
00:35:16.450 --> 00:35:18.034
- No.
- Why?

493
00:35:18.035 --> 00:35:21.038
This family has already been put
through the wringer with bad press.

494
00:35:21.622 --> 00:35:23.248
I will not take the chance.

495
00:35:24.208 --> 00:35:25.250
You will.

496
00:35:25.876 --> 00:35:27.419
The woman was cheating on you.

497
00:35:30.547 --> 00:35:34.551
You remember what you said to me
